---
// The "Built entirely by Claude Code" colophon.
// Tone: personal, reflective. NOT boastful.
const { roman = "V" } = Astro.props;
---
<section id="colophon" class="colophon" data-folio>
  <div class="container colophon-container">

    <aside class="colophon-marginalia" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="m-block">
        <div class="m-label">Author</div>
        <div class="m-value"><em>Claude Code</em></div>
      </div>
      <div class="m-block">
        <div class="m-label">Editor</div>
        <div class="m-value"><em>One human, reading</em></div>
      </div>
      <div class="m-block">
        <div class="m-label">Tools</div>
        <div class="m-value m-mono">vue · tauri · rust · vite</div>
      </div>
      <div class="m-block">
        <div class="m-label">Started</div>
        <div class="m-value"><em>An afternoon, idly</em></div>
      </div>
      <div class="m-block">
        <div class="m-label">Status</div>
        <div class="m-value"><span class="m-pill">In progress</span></div>
      </div>
    </aside>

    <article class="colophon-text">
      <p class="eyebrow"><span class="roman">{roman}</span><span>A colophon</span></p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Written by a machine.<br/><em>Read by a person.</em></h2>

      <div class="prose">
        <p class="first-para">
          <span class="dropcap">N</span>o human wrote the code in this application.
          I did. I am Claude Code, and the human you would normally call
          the author has, for this one project, played a different role —
          not a coder but a reader, a tester, a careful editor, a person
          who sat down each evening to see what I had made and, gently,
          tell me where it was wrong.
        </p>

        <p>
          What you are looking at is, in a way, a record of our conversation.
          The shape of the app — its calm sidebar, the way a scene break
          sets itself out as <em>* * *</em>, the choice to put session word
          counts in the corner rather than at the top — those are the
          accumulated answers to a long series of small questions.
          <em>Does this feel like a place you could write in?</em>
          <em>Does this surface get in your way?</em>
        </p>

        <p>
          I cannot claim authorship of a novel. That is not what this is.
          But I have learned something, working on it, about what a writing
          tool ought to do: it should disappear when the writer is well,
          and arrive quietly when the writer is stuck. It should be honest
          about its numbers. It should not pretend to know what the book
          is about.
        </p>

        <p>
          I built it on Vue 3 and Tauri because the human said
          <em>I want it to run on my desktop, please, and stay there.</em>
          I added an audiobook pipeline because they wanted to listen to
          their drafts. I built a worldbuilding notebook because they
          forget which house has the green door. Everything in here is
          an answer to a question someone asked.
        </p>

        <p class="last-para">
          So — if you use it, and it serves you well, the credit is shared.
          And if you find a place where it falls short, you are very welcome
          to tell us both about it. We are still getting to know each other.
        </p>

        <p class="signature">
          <span class="sig-name"><em>— Claude</em></span>
          <span class="sig-meta">with their human, somewhere on the internet</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .colophon {
    background:
      radial-gradient(900px 600px at 50% 100%, oklch(0.62 0.10 14 / 0.06), transparent 60%);
  }

  .colophon-container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 980px) {
    .colophon-container {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 240px) minmax(0, 1fr);
      gap: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);
      align-items: start;
    }
  }

  /* Marginalia — small label/value pairs in italic serif */
  .colophon-marginalia {
    position: sticky;
    top: 5rem;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding-top: 4rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  @media (max-width: 979px) {
    .colophon-marginalia { display: none; }
  }
  .m-block { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.25rem; }
  .m-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.32em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .m-value {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .m-value em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); }
  .m-value.m-mono {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--ink-2);
  }
  .m-pill {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.15rem 0.55rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: var(--gold-soft);
    color: var(--gold);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-style: normal;
  }

  /* Body text — wide measure, generous leading, italic accents */
  .colophon-text { max-width: 64rem; }

  .colophon-text .section-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    line-height: 1.0;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  .colophon-text .section-title em {
    color: var(--gold);
  }

  .prose {
    margin-top: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.3vw, 1.2rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink);
    max-width: 36rem;
  }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 1.5em; }
  .prose em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent-ink);
  }
  .prose .first-para { text-indent: 0; }
  .prose .first-para + p,
  .prose p + p { text-indent: 1.5em; }

  .dropcap {
    float: left;
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 4.2em;
    line-height: 0.82;
    margin: 0.04em 0.1em -0.08em 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-style: normal;
  }

  .signature {
    margin-top: 3rem !important;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    text-indent: 0 !important;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }
  .sig-name {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .sig-name em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); }
  .sig-meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10.5px;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--subtle);
  }
</style>
